reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Like the other reviews I think this product will greatly improve the stability of the truck when towing. Super easy to install the old foam things popped out and I put some soapy water on the new rubber supports and they popped right in. Then hopped in bed of truck and jump up and down to make sure they were seated. I will say like others have mentioned it does make for a rougher ride because the suspension doesn’t travel as far anymore but a trade off I’m willing make.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These should be stock! Of you haven't switched out the stock bump stops for these you most definitely should! I highly recommend to anyone that carries any weight or even just a simple canopy cover!!! Makes pulling the trailer feel much safer and less sway!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Received these same day which was great even though I had to update payment information. Would recommend to anyone that needs less sagging from towing a trailer. Thanks guys!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy Install and prevents my truck from sagging while towing
reviews.reviewText: These were easy to install on my 2020 RAM 1500. I didn't even have to jack up the truck. I put some hand soap on the top edge of each bump stop to make it easier to install. I still had to use a short pry bar to force them into the mount. Then I put a small piece of wood under each bump stop and got in the bed of the truck to make sure the bump stops were evenly installed. All good.The one minor issue has to do with the truck and the flat plate where the bump stops contact on the axle. On my RAM, the both plates have an angle on the leading edge and the bump stops hit that angled part just slightly before hitting the flat part. Doesn't seem to be a problem but just be aware if installing on a RAM 1500. Cheers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Simple to Install
reviews.reviewText: First of all…. These are awesome and were extremely easy to install. Once I popped the old bump stops off, I sprayed soapy water on these new bump stops and pushed them into place as much as I could. That part was a bit difficult and I couldn’t get them to pop into place. So, I took a small 2x4 and shaved two pieces down and put them under the bump stops on both sides and jumped up and down in the bed of the truck to make sure they were stuck in place. Unconventional? Absolutely…. Did it work??? Sure did!!!!!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars They hit hard and don't seem to flex.
reviews.reviewText: Per the directions, when you install these there will be 1/2"-1" between the bottom of the part and the frame. That space seems to be all the travel you get and then it hits hard and stops. I can't really tell if they flex past that point but they are really hard. They helped me tow my camper safely and reduced squat and sway so I guess it's a compromise. It is definitely not a comfortable ride.

reviews.reviewTitle: Great product works as it should
reviews.reviewText: Installed and works great had no issues, had to buff out mount hole to make sure they go into mount and stay. Put 4X4 timber between axle lowered truck and they bottomed and are staying there. Great price and product will buy again . Thanks
